{
  "stem": "868.4",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But as we came closer to each other, I realized it was Don Fascimeni, the director of the orphanage.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] When I was caught on the way to the farmhouse, the German-- one of the two accompanying us there-- went into abandoned houses along the way, and came out with what-- with whatever he could pilfer.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "At one time, he came out with a rabbit in a bag.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he gave me the rabbit to be carried on my shoulder.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that rabbit was digging frantically its nails into my-- my-- my back.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I now encounter Don Julio Fascimeni with that little boy.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He said, oh, my god.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Have they let you go?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I said, yes.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He said, I was in such fear for your life, because I had been told that you were caught with the others and that you were carrying a bag.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I thought that these were bags of weapons they had found stashed away in the orphanage.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I was sure they were going to execute you.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I was on my way there now, he said, to offer myself in exchange for your life.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Now, you must remember, I haven't spoken yet of Don Julio Fascimeni.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He was a man of infinite goodness.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And throughout my stay at the orphanage, we developed a close relationship.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Perhaps because he was empathizing with my situation as a Jewish refugee in a Catholic orphanage.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He was wonderful to all the boys, but especially to me and to Willy.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So that this gesture of him going to exchange himself was in keeping with his attitude.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we had developed a close relationship to the point that he was also a very sick man.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He had Parkinson's disease.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
